title: Root is required and that's a good thing!
comment: I've read reviews from people that rate 1/5 and say it'd be great if root wasn't required. This app works using the debug on a hardware level to access the wireless chip - think about that. The app is non-conventional in hardware usage; anything using debug (developer-device level tools) let alone directly accessing device internals should absolutely require root! (Malicious software, phishing, malware, spyware, etc. would have a field day bypassing Android's permissions!) Rooting adds risk..a user choice.

title: SnoopSnitch
comment: App seems to be working as advertised. YOU MUST pay special attention to the prerequisites before installing. They are rather unusual and not many users will meet the hardware and software requirements.  For instance, your phone must have a Qualcomm chipset. It also must be rooted. And finally, it should be running on stock Android 4.1 or later although some custom roms apparently work.  That being said, it should be noted that SRLabs should be commended for the effort. Same outfit that broke the BadUsb fiasco. They seem to be focused on awareness of issues like stingrays, etc as well as issues like BadUsb.  I'm not sure why some people can't get it to work. My first suggestion would be to make sure it's granted SU access. I know from experience that the request for SU access just flashes across the screen sometimes and if you're not looking you can miss it
